sentences: In the early 1990s, she developed Stanford's first course in digital audio coding, which eventually led to the publication of a textbook in the area.

In 2019, Marina Bosi was presented with the AES Silver Medal Award "in recognition of outstanding achievements in the development and standardization of audio and video coding and of secure digital rights management."
Marina Bosi and Richard E. Goldberg, Introduction to Digital Audio Coding and Standards, 2002.
